<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>No matter how much medical training you get you are still a man and will never be able to fully understand the amount stress and the full range of emotions that a wanted let alone an unwanted pregnancy brings.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Leah - I take exception to this comment as a sexist cop-out.  I am a father and I lay awake nights freaked out and stressed about my baby being healthy, were we eating right, reading right, doing everything we could.  Were they going to inherit my genetic defect or was I a carrier for things that I didn't even know about.  Was my dyslexia going to be profound and debilitating in them, or my allergies going to kill them.  What would I do if they were handicaped?  I have also been in the &quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>unwanted and powerless to do anything about it</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot; category when a woman tells you she is pregnant with your child and wants you to pay her for life and get a free ride from the military.  Men can get raped just as readily as women, it frequently goes unreported when it happens too.  We all have stresses, we all deal with them differently.  When my wife was pregnant, she was solid as the rock of ages compared to her sister (who freaks out when she farts now thinking it harms the baby.)  If a xian made the comment &quot;you aren't saved so you can't understand the peace of god&quot; it would be the same thing.  Beat him up with logic, clobber him with reason, but don't cop-out on the argument.  You're better than that. <p>DBC67<br>
