I think of the termination of life as I do of getting an F in school.  In other words I think that, regardless of the circumstances, it is a horrible thing.  Now in cases like rape/fatal diseases/developmental problems, I feel that that is like getting around a 46%.  While someone who wants to get an abortion for selfish reasons would be like getting a 6%.  Obviously I would rather the 46%.  Now I calssified rape along with diseases and developmental problems because, as I said before, it can lead to these problems.  As far as to why I make those distinctions, I don't know.  My subconcious mind is not that forthcoming with information on that subject.  <br>
<br>
Now that that is said, as a doctor,(or doctor in training. ie. med student) if an abortion is what I am required to do, then an abortion is what will be preformed.  I may not like the thought of the proceedure being preformed, but since it most likely will be, I would rather it done by a trained professional.  If the doctors were to refuse to preform that service, then some people would resort to untrained individuals who are willing to do it for a few bucks, but that would introduce a great risk to the patient while not changing the fact that the baby will be killed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luvthatdyl>LuvThatDyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 171<br> <font color=#3333ff>(6/13/03 5:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=213.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re:loss of life</span><hr size=1> I do understand what Phoenix has been saying.  Eventhough him and I don't necessarily agree on evaluating the circumstances for an abortion, I understand where he is coming from.  The most important thing is that he isn't taking a stance that can lead to preventing a woman from having an abortion.  He just merely has an opinion on the matter.  I understand the whole &quot;don't do the crime if you can't do the time&quot; philosophy, but my stance is that people are human and make mistakes, and many of those who make these mistakes are kids who sometimes lack the maturity to think through all the consequences.  I also appreciate the fact that Phoenix has made it clear he will put the needs of the patient in front of his own mere opinions.  That is original crux of this thread.  Some Catholic hospitals are putting their own agenda in front of the needs of their patients.  If I need medical care and I need to choose between the staunch Catholic and his list of rules or the ecclectic Wiccan who can put his opinions aside to help me, then that is an easy choice to make.  Unfortunately not many people get to make such a choice.<br>
<br>
Overall, I think Phoenix is just making a statement on why he would choose a certain path if he were in the situation.  Yes, I know he'll never get pregnant  But a lot of people think through how they would handle certain scenarios, even if they know they will never find themselves in the situation.  Of course, when it comes to abortion, nobody can really make any claims on what they would do unless they find themselves in the middle of the situation.  There have been women who make appointments to have an abortion and find themselves walking out of the clinic without having the procedure, and there are staunch pro-life activists who have a sudden change of heart when they find themselves in a state of desperation.  But eventhough we don't know exactly what we would do unless we were in the situation, we still form preliminary opinions on various matters, especially on controversial subjects that are constantly brought up as the subject of debate.<br>
<br>
Oh, and I do agree with the philosophy of many of the other posters here.  This is a general statement, and not a statement regarding Phoenix's post.  The whole argument of the pro-life camp is that they need to put the baby's life first.  I agree with people when they say that when it comes to the life of the baby, then the mode of conception shouldn't matter.  The life of a child conceived out of rape shouldn't be worth less than that of a child conceived out of consensual sex.  A lot of people who make the distinction are just looking to punish the mother for her &quot;sins&quot;.  There are some right wing politicians who say that rape isn't even an acceptable reason for an abortion.  Their reasoning is that &quot;a baby shouldn't be punished for the sins of the father&quot;.  While I think this is cruel and twisted, I have to at least give them credit for being consistent.  <br>
<br>
Stacey <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showMessageRange?topicID=213.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showMessageRange?topicID=213.topic&start=41&stop=41>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=213.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showNextMessage?topicID=213.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=213.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/bluesparty/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.emailToFriend?topicID=213.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.threadControl?topicID=213.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/bluesparty/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=213.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=213.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notific